A few months ago, I was in a group chat with friends talking about some of the amazing stuff LLMs do.
I told them that I don&rsquo;t do any &ldquo;vibe coding&rdquo;, that is, the building of software exclusively via prompting LLM tools like Cursor. To me LLMs are more of a research tool like Stack Overflow. I ask it questions about stuff I want to do.
It is something for filling my gaps in knowledge. So at the end of the day, I often prefer my own judgement &amp; style. As I don&rsquo;t think vibe coding is an advantage.
I will try to describe my reasons why.
1. The economics world is a minority game. # Knowledge work like software development only has value when you know what other people don&rsquo;t. 1
Not many people will pay you a premium for knowing what everyone can &ldquo;vibe code&rdquo;.
So you&rsquo;re better off learning something hard that LLMs won&rsquo;t be able to do.
2. Vibe Coding is the WYSIWYG of the 2020&rsquo;s # I remember when learning web development in high school and asked my friends why they were stressing with HTML instead of just using Dream Weaver, WiX or Microsoft Publisher — The so called WYSIWYG tools (What You See Is What You Get) that utilized drag and drop for building websites. 2
They simply replied with &ldquo;HTML is better&rdquo;. The answer didn&rsquo;t make sense to me then.
But now I think I know the answer. Writing your own code instead of using a WYSIWYG gives you fine-grained control of what your working on.
Think of vibe coding like buying a cake mix (pre-mixed ingredients for making a cake) for running a bakery instead of inventing your own recipes.
Inventing your own cake recipe is hard and slow. But think of everyone else buying the same cake mix to run their bakery.
The icing on the cakes might look different but the taste will be the same. So the differentiating factor amongst competitors will be very little.
I think LLMs will be like spreadsheets for programmers.
Spreadsheets didn&rsquo;t give normal people CPA level skills, but they did improve the normal persons book keeping skills.
3. Might cause atrophy of temporal logic. # Atrophy is a biological condition where the body reduces the size and there for effectiveness of an organ. 3
This often happens when that organ is not used as much. So maybe the body wastes it way internationally as it may not &ldquo;want&rdquo; to keep on maintaining something that it isn&rsquo;t using.
This happens with muscles. So when you stop working out at the gym your muscles start disappearing.
What worries me is that this may happen to skilled programmers brains. The developed faculties of the brain concerning temporal logic 4 might be wasted away such that;
a) Other tasks that might have benefited from your &ldquo;programming cognitive muscles&rdquo; might get harder to do.
b) It might get harder to learn a new &ldquo;programming like&rdquo; skill that shows up in the future.
In London for example, they have a taxi service informally referred to as &ldquo;Black Cabs&rdquo;.
It turns out that in order to work for these &ldquo;Black Cabs&rdquo; you are required to memorize over 40,000 streets and landmarks and major buildings. 5
People who qualify to drive for black cabs often develop a bigger hippocampus (part if the brain responsible for memory), and this bigger hippocampus probably helps them memorize stuff more effectively compared to Uber drivers that rely on GPS 6 — a better memory system will also be beneficial to the black cab drivers for tasks that have nothing to do with driving, but require good memory.
4. The &ldquo;Vibed Code&rdquo; may not be your vibe # Below is C code by Arthur Whitney for the J compiler 7. This coding style is something that you will find in the Array language community.
